ic bike offerings and distribution so weak  their dealers are true cycling enthusiasts who frequently started their bike shop because of that passion the vast majority of traditional bike shops today however tend to think of electric bikes as a form of cheatingthis trickles down the entire supply chain a bike company may have only  or  electric bike models resulting in limited choice bike shop owners and staff are not thrilled about selling electricpowered products customers typically start their ebike research online rather than by going to a local storegiven all of this if you visit any traditional bike store and ask them about their electric bike distribution they will either have no interest or they will say that they tried but couldn’t really find a way to sell a meaningful number of ebikeseven with traditional bike companies not finding a viable market for electric bikes we still take steps to differentiate ourselves  laser focus on electric bikes and directtoconsumer distribution we only sell electric bikes making us the natural choice for customers looking for one based on our findings many people begin their research on electric bikes online rather than by going to a traditional store this allows us to capture their attention and trust first in terms of distribution traditional bike brands are inflexible given that they have to rely on an existing network of dealers as a result any bike sold directly at a brickandmortar dealer carries a markup of up to  over a directtoconsumer brand like ours this allows us to offer a lower price to the customer while maintaining a higher profit margin  electric bike companies eg pedego stromer faraday with competing electric bike companies we focus on the ways we can win over a customer  technology  although there is no such thing as a perfect bike for everyone certain technological features do make a bike more appealing to a wider population  automatic transmission  many of our customers are new to cycling so we focus on making our products incredibly easy to use with no learning curve for example many customers tell us that they dislike the traditional gearing mechanisms used on bikes consequently we have done away with traditional gearing by using the nuvinci harmony cvt instead this is basically an automatic transmission like we find in cars but designed for a bike changing the gears for the rider automatically httpwwwevelocomevelodifferencenuvinciharmonyautomatictransmission  middrive motor design  we also chose a different motor design than most other ebike companies they use traditional hub motors because they are cheaper and easier to source instead we offer a middrive option this offers a lot of advantages better climbing of the hills better range ability to use a smaller battery and still get great range and being able to take advantage of all of the gears on a bike httpwwwevelocomevelodifferenceadvantagesmiddrivemotorvshubmotor the use of a middrive motor combined with the nuvinci harmony is a major draw for many of our customers  omni wheel  in addition to a line of complete electric bikes we recently launched the new omni wheel httpomnievelocom by replacing the front wheel with the omni anyone can convert a traditional bike into an electric one in just  minutes no technical skills are required and it comes at a fraction of the price of a complete bike with the addition of the omni wheel we can meet the needs of virtually any customer at any price point  distribution  technology is only  of the equation even if we had the best bike tech out there if we cant sell it at the right price point to the right customer we would still be out of luck  directtoconsumer distribution model – selling directly to customers in an online marketplace lets us consistently price our products at  less than brands at brickandmortar stores while also offering a better overall product more power more range this allows us to scale faster and more efficiently such that with modest increases in tea