owth in a capitalintensive business such as evelo’s with a goal of achieving economies of scale to slingshot even greater opportunities we need additional capital over the past couple of years we have finetuned our advertising efforts our logistics purchasing etc  learning what works what doesnt and how to keep costs down fast growth at this point depends on focusing on customer acquisition to increase our volume with our suppliers which will actually drive down production costs its winwin situation  more customers mean we can produce our product for less and we can sell it for less which in turn will attract more customers once we go from  million to about  million in sales we’ll start seeing significant drops in our production costs for those that are completely unfamiliar with your space can you talk about what the market looks like and where you see it going in the next  years one of the things we joke about internally is that an electric bike is the bestselling electric vehicle in the world that nobody in the us knows about although the global electric bike market involves  billion a year with  million electric bikes sold last year and a growth rate of  yearoveryear the market in the us lags behind the rest of the world some companies that started out  years before we did now reach sales of  to  million per year some impressive growth in the us market during the past year or so however makes this the perfect time for us to expand in the us interest in electric bikes is fuelled by three major trends the first is the search for alternative means of transport in growing urban centers where car ownership is expensive parking space limited and rushhour traffic leads to gridlock second electric transport in general is becoming mainstream for environmental and other reasons tesla’s entry into the electric vehicle field succeeded in bringing together technology that is acceptably priced of proven quality and visually attractive – paving the way for increased general interest in alternative transport as a whole the third trend is a growing emphasis on staying health fit and active with a large number of baby boomers now hitting retirement age staying active and fit may involve agerelated challenges that electric bikes help overcome over the next five years even as electric and hybrid cars become more the norm some people will still choose an electric bike for most travel especially as urban areas continue to develop more of a biking culture with increased use of dedicated bike lanes and trails zipping past rushhour traffic will still be appealing whether the cars in traffic are gas powered or electric and of course an electric bike still will help older riders keep fit and active something that is beyond the capabilities of an electric car lifestyle choices offered by electric bikes such as leisurely rides on trails and paths a secondary transportation device for rv owners and quickandeasy errandrunning will greatly expand in essence the presence of electric and hybrid cars in the market will be a catalyst for growing interest in other environmentfriendly options like electric bikes we see nothing but growth here in the us as well as some interesting opportunities in other areas of the world what’s next for your business and why are you raising money now up until now weve been bootstrapping with a goal of getting the fundamentals right we have succeeded in developing a directtoconsumer model in an industry that traditionally does not take that approach we have worked on bringing down our acquisition costs our rd costs and finetuned the ecommerce side of things although there is always more to learn were on the right track the next step is ramping up growth first by bringing new products to the market to that end we are involved in the internal development of a new product that will be for sale early in  we also plan to introduce new and recurring revenue streams starting with the bikeasaservice approach that i mentioned earlier options like theft protection or annual maintenance plans are a real opportunity to turn a  onetime bike purchase into a monthly subscription to additional service offerings at the same time we intend to venture outside of the us market beginning with expansion into canada next year with a similar market and geography expansion into canada carries limited risk and lets us finetune our distribution techniques by applying these same techniques to the much larger european market we will find a profitable niche there that features competitive pricing at  euros less than european pricing what’s been your largest challenge so far ironically enough our biggest challenge came from our major strength  offering a directtoconsumer model most of the packaging used in the bike industry isn’t designed to effectively protect the product when individual boxes are shipped to customers via costeffective shippers like fedex or ups at first we experienced significant damage on up to  of shipped bikes resulting from transit through various hubs or centers on its way to its destination as well as sometimes lessthanstellar treatment during the final trip to the customer’s door obviously this is a poor customer experience and is very costly to deal with even in cases where our damage claims were accepted by the shipper we needed another solution so we experimented with designing packaging that would survive and protect the bike no matter what ups or fedex could throw at it with that challenge solved shipping damage affects less than half a percent of orders fewer than  in  bikes this is an unusual fundraising strategy why have you given your customers the chance to invest online via wefunder we did a small friends and familyseed round last year and also emailed our customer base about our vision for the company we were blown away by the degree of interest – in fact two customers wound up investing around  but last year we had to turn away many potential investors because they were not accred